    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Brass-studded prestige X-chairs of the Asante people of Africa, having arms, openwork backs, and legs that cross diagonally; the leg configuration is based on European folding chairs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sillas X de prestigio adornadas con clavos de bronce del pueblo Asante de África, que tienen brazos, respaldos calados y patas cruzadas diagonalmente, la disposición de las patas se basa en las sillas plegables europeas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Met  koper beslagen prestigieuze X-framestoelen van het Afrikaanse Asantevolk, met armleuningen een ajour bewerkte rug en diagonaal gekruiste poten; de vorm van de poten is afgeleid van Europese vouwstoelen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Messingbeschlagener, prestigeträchtiger Scherenstuhl des afrikanischen Volkes der Aschanti, der über Armlehnen, eine Rückenlehne mit Lochmuster und diagonal gekreuzte Beine verfügt; die Beinstellung leitet sich vom europäischen Klappstuhl ab.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>非洲阿桑特人的X形椅，通常佈滿銅釘，備有扶手，椅背呈網狀，椅腳則相互交叉；椅腳的結構以歐洲摺疊椅為根據。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
